    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="124"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 France/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The French Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation<note n="23" xml:id="d124fn23">File
                            translation revised.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: With special reference to Your
                    Excellency’s note of April 22, last,<note n="24" xml:id="d124fn24">Not
                        printed.</note> I have, by order of my Government, the honor to inform you
                    that Mr. Parmentier, Director of the General Handling of Funds of the Ministry
                    of Finance, has been commissioned to enter into relations with the American
                    Commission on War Foreign Debts. He will shortly sail for the United States on
                    board <hi rend="italic">La Savoie.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>He will be accompanied by Mr. Le Neveu, Secretary of Embassy, assigned for duty
                    at the Ministry of Commerce.</p>
                <p>Be pleased [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>P. S. I should be very thankful to the Department of State if you would
                        kindly direct that the necessary steps be taken to facilitate the landing of
                        these two French citizens sent on a mission to the United States. J.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
